 :tx/rationale "SECOND ROOT CAUSE: write_slim_cache() fingerprint includes hashes not in store.bin. At layout.rs:569, write_slim_cache() calls list_tx_hashes() to compute the meta.json fingerprint. This lists ALL .edn files on disk — including ones written by OTHER LiveStore instances that the flushing instance never loaded. Result: meta.json says 'I represent files A,B,C,D' but store.bin only contains datoms from A,B,C. The next reader computes fingerprint(A,B,C,D), matches meta.json → CACHE HIT → loads stale store.bin missing D's datoms. The fingerprint check was DESIGNED to detect staleness but it CAUSES staleness because it reads the filesystem (which includes all files) but pairs it with an in-memory store (which only has files known at open time). This is the fundamental invariant violation: INV-STORE-020 says 'After flush, store.bin equals fold(txn_files)'. The fingerprint makes the NEXT reader BELIEVE this is true when it is not."
